[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":690},["ShallowReactive",2],{"content-query-yYmyWuTGZa":3},{"_path":4,"_dir":5,"_draft":6,"_partial":6,"_locale":7,"title":8,"description":9,"tutor":10,"time":11,"video":6,"topics":12,"content":15,"readingTime":109,"body":114,"_type":683,"_id":684,"_source":685,"_file":686,"_stem":687,"_extension":688,"sitemap":689},"/courses/02-frontend-system-design","courses",false,"","Frontend System Design","This course is designed to take you from Zero to Hero in Frontend System Design. Through a combination of in-depth tutorials and practical, real-world examples, you’ll gain hands-on experience in designing scalable and efficient frontend architectures. The curriculum follows a ‘learn by doing’ approach, ensuring that even the most complex topics are grounded in real application scenarios. Whether you're aiming to build robust frontend systems or preparing for your next Frontend System Design interview, this course equips you with the skills and confidence to succeed. Start your journey today.",1,"5hr 30 mins",[13,14],"nodejs","javascript",[16,65],{"module_id":10,"module_name":17,"module_duration":18,"topics_count":19,"tutor":10,"expanded":6,"topics":20},"Networking","40 mins read",5,[21,30,39,48,57],{"id":10,"topic_name":22,"sub_topic":17,"publish_date":23,"description":24,"topics":25,"duration":26,"photo_url":27,"auther_name":28,"is_on_youtube":6,"_path":29},"How the Web Works","2025-03-01","Network is a core part of software, as the frontend needs data and the backend sends it. All of this happens through the network. How is data transferred over the internet? How does it reach the client, and what protocols are required? These are essential concepts for software development. We need to understand what happens when we type \"google.com,\" what DNS is, and its role in the process.\n",[13,14],"14:00 mins read","https://res.cloudinary.com/duojkrgue/image/upload/v1744045763/Portfolio/FrontendSystemDesignCourse/1_lxnuab.png","Rahul Aher","frontend-system-design-1-1",{"id":31,"topic_name":32,"sub_topic":17,"publish_date":33,"description":34,"topics":35,"duration":36,"photo_url":37,"auther_name":28,"is_on_youtube":6,"_path":38},2,"Communication Protocols","2025-03-02","A communications protocol is a set of formal rules describing how to transmit or exchange data, especially across a network. A standardised communications protocol is one that has been codified as a standard. Examples of these include WiFi, the Internet Protocol, and the Hypertext Transfer Protocol (HTTP).\n",[13,14],"3:00 mins read","https://res.cloudinary.com/duojkrgue/image/upload/v1744045766/Portfolio/FrontendSystemDesignCourse/2_qlrcpc.png","frontend-system-design-1-2",{"id":40,"topic_name":41,"sub_topic":17,"publish_date":42,"description":43,"topics":44,"duration":45,"photo_url":46,"auther_name":28,"is_on_youtube":6,"_path":47},3,"HTTP Headers Methods Status Codes and Rest API Deep Dive","2025-03-03","If you are a junior developer, a senior developer, or just a complete newbie, this is going to be a great place to learn about REST APIs—what they are, why they are used, and how they work. This is going to be a long blog, so it’s for serious readers. If you prefer short TikTok-like videos for instant information, this might not be for you. Let’s get started!\n",[13,14],"22:00 mins read","https://res.cloudinary.com/duojkrgue/image/upload/v1744045770/Portfolio/FrontendSystemDesignCourse/3_sskfuy.png","frontend-system-design-1-3",{"id":49,"topic_name":50,"sub_topic":17,"publish_date":51,"description":52,"topics":53,"duration":54,"photo_url":55,"auther_name":28,"is_on_youtube":6,"_path":56},4,"Why GraphQL over Rest APIs","2025-03-04","Many companies today use GraphQL. In this blog, we’ll explore what GraphQL is, its benefits, and why it’s so popular. Suppose your app needs information about continents, countries, and languages. If you’re using REST APIs, you’ll likely call multiple APIs to fetch this data and then organize it for your frontend. Be patient—it’s not an Instagram Reel, but for serious learners, it’ll be worth the read.\n",[13,14],"11:00 mins read","https://res.cloudinary.com/duojkrgue/image/upload/v1744045780/Portfolio/FrontendSystemDesignCourse/4_iildzs.png","frontend-system-design-1-4",{"id":19,"topic_name":58,"sub_topic":17,"publish_date":59,"description":60,"topics":61,"duration":62,"photo_url":63,"auther_name":28,"is_on_youtube":6,"_path":64},"A quick overview of gRPC","2025-03-05","It's kind of like a sibling to REST API or GraphQL, enabling communication with the server in a unique way. RPC stands for Remote Procedure Call, and the \"g\" in gRPC stands for Google, as it was created by Google.\n",[13,14],"6.00 mins read","https://res.cloudinary.com/duojkrgue/image/upload/v1744045783/Portfolio/FrontendSystemDesignCourse/5_uc5xlf.png","frontend-system-design-1-5",{"module_id":31,"module_name":66,"module_duration":67,"topics_count":19,"tutor":10,"expanded":6,"topics":68},"Communication","35 mins read",[69,77,85,93,101],{"id":70,"topic_name":71,"sub_topic":17,"publish_date":72,"description":73,"topics":74,"duration":26,"photo_url":75,"auther_name":28,"is_on_youtube":6,"_path":76},6,"What is short polling? Learn with example","2025-03-06","Dive into short polling methodologies. Explore the technique of frequent requests to servers at fixed intervals, enabling frontend applications to obtain recent data updates for dynamic content.\n",[13,14],"https://res.cloudinary.com/duojkrgue/image/upload/v1744108647/Portfolio/FrontendSystemDesignCourse/6_llcndo.png","frontend-system-design-2-1",{"id":78,"topic_name":79,"sub_topic":17,"publish_date":80,"description":81,"topics":82,"duration":36,"photo_url":83,"auther_name":28,"is_on_youtube":6,"_path":84},7,"Practical Guide Long Polling","2025-03-07","Explore long polling techniques. Learn how continuous connections to servers facilitate real-time data updates, enabling frontend applications to receive immediate data upon availability, optimizing user experiences.\n",[13,14],"https://res.cloudinary.com/duojkrgue/image/upload/v1744108670/Portfolio/FrontendSystemDesignCourse/7_y3axa8.png","frontend-system-design-2-2",{"id":86,"topic_name":87,"sub_topic":17,"publish_date":88,"description":89,"topics":90,"duration":45,"photo_url":91,"auther_name":28,"is_on_youtube":6,"_path":92},8,"Web Socket","2025-03-08","Discover the power of Web Sockets. Learn to establish persistent connections facilitating real-time, bidirectional communication between clients and servers, enhancing interactivity and responsiveness in frontend applications.\n",[13,14],"https://res.cloudinary.com/duojkrgue/image/upload/v1744108685/Portfolio/FrontendSystemDesignCourse/8_botlhe.png","frontend-system-design-2-3",{"id":94,"topic_name":95,"sub_topic":17,"publish_date":96,"description":97,"topics":98,"duration":54,"photo_url":99,"auther_name":28,"is_on_youtube":6,"_path":100},9,"Server Sent Events - A Real time communication","2025-03-09","Delve into Server-Sent Events. Understand how servers push data to clients, enabling continuous updates in frontend applications without the need for repeated requests, optimizing data streaming.\n",[13,14],"https://res.cloudinary.com/duojkrgue/image/upload/v1744108696/Portfolio/FrontendSystemDesignCourse/9_fvmoja.png","frontend-system-design-2-4",{"id":102,"topic_name":103,"sub_topic":17,"publish_date":104,"description":105,"topics":106,"duration":62,"photo_url":107,"auther_name":28,"is_on_youtube":6,"_path":108},10,"Introduction to Web hooks","2025-03-10","Understand WebHooks' functionalities. Learn how they trigger instant notifications and events, allowing frontend systems to react promptly to external changes or specific actions, ensuring responsiveness and agility.\n",[13,14],"https://res.cloudinary.com/duojkrgue/image/upload/v1744108709/Portfolio/FrontendSystemDesignCourse/10_ahspdw.png","frontend-system-design-2-5",{"text":110,"minutes":111,"time":112,"words":113},"3 min read",2.745,164700,549,{"type":115,"children":116,"toc":661},"root",[117,126,140,146,151,163,169,174,239,244,250,262,309,320,333,343,366,377,417,428,441,451,459,465,470,592,598,641,647,652,656],{"type":118,"tag":119,"props":120,"children":122},"element","h2",{"id":121},"what-is-system-design",[123],{"type":124,"value":125},"text","What is System Design?",{"type":118,"tag":127,"props":128,"children":129},"p",{},[130,132,138],{"type":124,"value":131},"In the world of software engineering, ",{"type":118,"tag":133,"props":134,"children":135},"strong",{},[136],{"type":124,"value":137},"system design",{"type":124,"value":139}," is a critical skill that bridges the gap between abstract ideas and functional, scalable solutions. Whether you're building a small web application or architecting a complex distributed system, understanding system design is essential. This blog explores what system design is, why it's important, and how to approach it effectively.",{"type":118,"tag":119,"props":141,"children":143},{"id":142},"defining-system-design",[144],{"type":124,"value":145},"Defining System Design",{"type":118,"tag":127,"props":147,"children":148},{},[149],{"type":124,"value":150},"System design refers to the process of defining the architecture, components, modules, interfaces, and data flow of a system to meet specific requirements. It involves making high-level decisions about how the system will function and ensuring it can handle the expected workload efficiently.",{"type":118,"tag":127,"props":152,"children":153},{},[154,156,161],{"type":124,"value":155},"In simpler terms, system design is the ",{"type":118,"tag":133,"props":157,"children":158},{},[159],{"type":124,"value":160},"blueprint for building software systems",{"type":124,"value":162},". It takes into account scalability, reliability, security, and performance, ensuring that the system can meet both current and future demands.",{"type":118,"tag":119,"props":164,"children":166},{"id":165},"why-system-design-matters",[167],{"type":124,"value":168},"Why System Design Matters",{"type":118,"tag":127,"props":170,"children":171},{},[172],{"type":124,"value":173},"System design is the backbone of any robust software solution. Here’s why it’s crucial:",{"type":118,"tag":175,"props":176,"children":177},"ol",{},[178,189,199,209,219,229],{"type":118,"tag":179,"props":180,"children":181},"li",{},[182,187],{"type":118,"tag":133,"props":183,"children":184},{},[185],{"type":124,"value":186},"Scalability",{"type":124,"value":188},": A well-designed system can handle increasing traffic or data without breaking.",{"type":118,"tag":179,"props":190,"children":191},{},[192,197],{"type":118,"tag":133,"props":193,"children":194},{},[195],{"type":124,"value":196},"Reliability",{"type":124,"value":198},": Ensures the system remains functional and available, even during failures or high loads.",{"type":118,"tag":179,"props":200,"children":201},{},[202,207],{"type":118,"tag":133,"props":203,"children":204},{},[205],{"type":124,"value":206},"Maintainability",{"type":124,"value":208},": Simplifies debugging, adding new features, and making changes over time.",{"type":118,"tag":179,"props":210,"children":211},{},[212,217],{"type":118,"tag":133,"props":213,"children":214},{},[215],{"type":124,"value":216},"Performance Optimization",{"type":124,"value":218},": A good design minimizes latency and maximizes resource efficiency.",{"type":118,"tag":179,"props":220,"children":221},{},[222,227],{"type":118,"tag":133,"props":223,"children":224},{},[225],{"type":124,"value":226},"Security",{"type":124,"value":228},": Protects sensitive data and prevents vulnerabilities.",{"type":118,"tag":179,"props":230,"children":231},{},[232,237],{"type":118,"tag":133,"props":233,"children":234},{},[235],{"type":124,"value":236},"User Experience",{"type":124,"value":238},": A well-designed system delivers seamless and fast interactions for users.",{"type":118,"tag":127,"props":240,"children":241},{},[242],{"type":124,"value":243},"For engineers, system design demonstrates the ability to think holistically and solve real-world problems effectively.",{"type":118,"tag":119,"props":245,"children":247},{"id":246},"key-concepts-in-system-design",[248],{"type":124,"value":249},"Key Concepts in System Design",{"type":118,"tag":251,"props":252,"children":254},"h3",{"id":253},"_1-architecture",[255,257],{"type":124,"value":256},"1. ",{"type":118,"tag":133,"props":258,"children":259},{},[260],{"type":124,"value":261},"Architecture",{"type":118,"tag":263,"props":264,"children":265},"ul",{},[266,271],{"type":118,"tag":179,"props":267,"children":268},{},[269],{"type":124,"value":270},"Defines the overall structure of the system.",{"type":118,"tag":179,"props":272,"children":273},{},[274,276],{"type":124,"value":275},"Common types include:\n",{"type":118,"tag":263,"props":277,"children":278},{},[279,289,299],{"type":118,"tag":179,"props":280,"children":281},{},[282,287],{"type":118,"tag":133,"props":283,"children":284},{},[285],{"type":124,"value":286},"Monolithic Architecture",{"type":124,"value":288},": A single, unified system.",{"type":118,"tag":179,"props":290,"children":291},{},[292,297],{"type":118,"tag":133,"props":293,"children":294},{},[295],{"type":124,"value":296},"Microservices Architecture",{"type":124,"value":298},": A system composed of smaller, independent services.",{"type":118,"tag":179,"props":300,"children":301},{},[302,307],{"type":118,"tag":133,"props":303,"children":304},{},[305],{"type":124,"value":306},"Serverless Architecture",{"type":124,"value":308},": Relies on third-party cloud services to execute code.",{"type":118,"tag":251,"props":310,"children":312},{"id":311},"_2-components",[313,315],{"type":124,"value":314},"2. ",{"type":118,"tag":133,"props":316,"children":317},{},[318],{"type":124,"value":319},"Components",{"type":118,"tag":263,"props":321,"children":322},{},[323,328],{"type":118,"tag":179,"props":324,"children":325},{},[326],{"type":124,"value":327},"Key building blocks like databases, servers, APIs, and load balancers.",{"type":118,"tag":179,"props":329,"children":330},{},[331],{"type":124,"value":332},"These components work together to achieve system functionality.",{"type":118,"tag":251,"props":334,"children":336},{"id":335},"_3-scalability",[337,339],{"type":124,"value":338},"3. ",{"type":118,"tag":133,"props":340,"children":341},{},[342],{"type":124,"value":186},{"type":118,"tag":263,"props":344,"children":345},{},[346,356],{"type":118,"tag":179,"props":347,"children":348},{},[349,354],{"type":118,"tag":133,"props":350,"children":351},{},[352],{"type":124,"value":353},"Horizontal Scaling",{"type":124,"value":355},": Adding more servers or instances.",{"type":118,"tag":179,"props":357,"children":358},{},[359,364],{"type":118,"tag":133,"props":360,"children":361},{},[362],{"type":124,"value":363},"Vertical Scaling",{"type":124,"value":365},": Adding more resources (CPU, RAM) to a single server.",{"type":118,"tag":251,"props":367,"children":369},{"id":368},"_4-data-flow",[370,372],{"type":124,"value":371},"4. ",{"type":118,"tag":133,"props":373,"children":374},{},[375],{"type":124,"value":376},"Data Flow",{"type":118,"tag":263,"props":378,"children":379},{},[380],{"type":118,"tag":179,"props":381,"children":382},{},[383,385],{"type":124,"value":384},"How data moves within the system, including:\n",{"type":118,"tag":263,"props":386,"children":387},{},[388,398,408],{"type":118,"tag":179,"props":389,"children":390},{},[391,396],{"type":118,"tag":133,"props":392,"children":393},{},[394],{"type":124,"value":395},"User requests",{"type":124,"value":397}," (e.g., via REST APIs or GraphQL).",{"type":118,"tag":179,"props":399,"children":400},{},[401,406],{"type":118,"tag":133,"props":402,"children":403},{},[404],{"type":124,"value":405},"Backend processing",{"type":124,"value":407},".",{"type":118,"tag":179,"props":409,"children":410},{},[411,416],{"type":118,"tag":133,"props":412,"children":413},{},[414],{"type":124,"value":415},"Database interactions",{"type":124,"value":407},{"type":118,"tag":251,"props":418,"children":420},{"id":419},"_5-database-design",[421,423],{"type":124,"value":422},"5. ",{"type":118,"tag":133,"props":424,"children":425},{},[426],{"type":124,"value":427},"Database Design",{"type":118,"tag":263,"props":429,"children":430},{},[431,436],{"type":118,"tag":179,"props":432,"children":433},{},[434],{"type":124,"value":435},"Choosing between SQL (e.g., MySQL, PostgreSQL) and NoSQL (e.g., MongoDB, DynamoDB).",{"type":118,"tag":179,"props":437,"children":438},{},[439],{"type":124,"value":440},"Optimizing for read/write operations and designing efficient schemas.",{"type":118,"tag":251,"props":442,"children":444},{"id":443},"_6-reliability",[445,447],{"type":124,"value":446},"6. ",{"type":118,"tag":133,"props":448,"children":449},{},[450],{"type":124,"value":196},{"type":118,"tag":263,"props":452,"children":453},{},[454],{"type":118,"tag":179,"props":455,"children":456},{},[457],{"type":124,"value":458},"Includes failover mechanisms, redundancy, and backups to ensure high availability.",{"type":118,"tag":119,"props":460,"children":462},{"id":461},"how-to-approach-system-design",[463],{"type":124,"value":464},"How to Approach System Design",{"type":118,"tag":127,"props":466,"children":467},{},[468],{"type":124,"value":469},"Here’s a step-by-step guide to tackle system design effectively:",{"type":118,"tag":175,"props":471,"children":472},{},[473,494,510,544,560,576],{"type":118,"tag":179,"props":474,"children":475},{},[476,481],{"type":118,"tag":133,"props":477,"children":478},{},[479],{"type":124,"value":480},"Understand the Requirements",{"type":118,"tag":263,"props":482,"children":483},{},[484,489],{"type":118,"tag":179,"props":485,"children":486},{},[487],{"type":124,"value":488},"Identify functional requirements (what the system should do).",{"type":118,"tag":179,"props":490,"children":491},{},[492],{"type":124,"value":493},"Identify non-functional requirements (scalability, latency, uptime, etc.).",{"type":118,"tag":179,"props":495,"children":496},{},[497,502],{"type":118,"tag":133,"props":498,"children":499},{},[500],{"type":124,"value":501},"Define the Core Components",{"type":118,"tag":263,"props":503,"children":504},{},[505],{"type":118,"tag":179,"props":506,"children":507},{},[508],{"type":124,"value":509},"Break down the system into manageable pieces like frontend, backend, databases, caching layers, and load balancers.",{"type":118,"tag":179,"props":511,"children":512},{},[513,518],{"type":118,"tag":133,"props":514,"children":515},{},[516],{"type":124,"value":517},"Choose the Right Tools",{"type":118,"tag":263,"props":519,"children":520},{},[521],{"type":118,"tag":179,"props":522,"children":523},{},[524,526],{"type":124,"value":525},"Select technologies and services based on requirements:\n",{"type":118,"tag":263,"props":527,"children":528},{},[529,534,539],{"type":118,"tag":179,"props":530,"children":531},{},[532],{"type":124,"value":533},"Programming languages (e.g., Python, Java).",{"type":118,"tag":179,"props":535,"children":536},{},[537],{"type":124,"value":538},"Cloud services (e.g., AWS, Azure, GCP).",{"type":118,"tag":179,"props":540,"children":541},{},[542],{"type":124,"value":543},"Databases (e.g., SQL, NoSQL).",{"type":118,"tag":179,"props":545,"children":546},{},[547,552],{"type":118,"tag":133,"props":548,"children":549},{},[550],{"type":124,"value":551},"Design for Scalability and Reliability",{"type":118,"tag":263,"props":553,"children":554},{},[555],{"type":118,"tag":179,"props":556,"children":557},{},[558],{"type":124,"value":559},"Use load balancing and distributed databases to handle scale.",{"type":118,"tag":179,"props":561,"children":562},{},[563,568],{"type":118,"tag":133,"props":564,"children":565},{},[566],{"type":124,"value":567},"Visualize the System",{"type":118,"tag":263,"props":569,"children":570},{},[571],{"type":118,"tag":179,"props":572,"children":573},{},[574],{"type":124,"value":575},"Create architecture diagrams to map out components and data flow.",{"type":118,"tag":179,"props":577,"children":578},{},[579,584],{"type":118,"tag":133,"props":580,"children":581},{},[582],{"type":124,"value":583},"Iterate and Optimize",{"type":118,"tag":263,"props":585,"children":586},{},[587],{"type":118,"tag":179,"props":588,"children":589},{},[590],{"type":124,"value":591},"Identify bottlenecks, optimize performance, and refine the design as needed.",{"type":118,"tag":119,"props":593,"children":595},{"id":594},"common-scenarios-in-system-design",[596],{"type":124,"value":597},"Common Scenarios in System Design",{"type":118,"tag":263,"props":599,"children":600},{},[601,611,621,631],{"type":118,"tag":179,"props":602,"children":603},{},[604,609],{"type":118,"tag":133,"props":605,"children":606},{},[607],{"type":124,"value":608},"URL Shortener",{"type":124,"value":610},": Focus on unique URL generation, database storage, and high availability.",{"type":118,"tag":179,"props":612,"children":613},{},[614,619],{"type":118,"tag":133,"props":615,"children":616},{},[617],{"type":124,"value":618},"Messaging System",{"type":124,"value":620},": Emphasize real-time delivery, scalability, and persistence.",{"type":118,"tag":179,"props":622,"children":623},{},[624,629],{"type":118,"tag":133,"props":625,"children":626},{},[627],{"type":124,"value":628},"E-Commerce Platform",{"type":124,"value":630},": Handle user authentication, inventory management, and payment processing.",{"type":118,"tag":179,"props":632,"children":633},{},[634,639],{"type":118,"tag":133,"props":635,"children":636},{},[637],{"type":124,"value":638},"Video Streaming Platform",{"type":124,"value":640},": Optimize content delivery, buffering, and scalability.",{"type":118,"tag":119,"props":642,"children":644},{"id":643},"conclusion",[645],{"type":124,"value":646},"Conclusion",{"type":118,"tag":127,"props":648,"children":649},{},[650],{"type":124,"value":651},"System design is both an art and a science. By mastering its principles, you can create applications that are scalable, reliable, and efficient—ensuring a seamless experience for users and long-term success for your organization.",{"type":118,"tag":653,"props":654,"children":655},"hr",{},[],{"type":118,"tag":127,"props":657,"children":658},{},[659],{"type":124,"value":660},"Thank you so much for reading. If you found it valuable, consider subscribing for more such content every week. If you have any questions or suggestions, please email me your comments or feel free to improve it.",{"title":7,"searchDepth":31,"depth":31,"links":662},[663,664,665,666,680,681,682],{"id":121,"depth":31,"text":125},{"id":142,"depth":31,"text":145},{"id":165,"depth":31,"text":168},{"id":246,"depth":31,"text":249,"children":667},[668,670,672,674,676,678],{"id":253,"depth":40,"text":669},"1. Architecture",{"id":311,"depth":40,"text":671},"2. Components",{"id":335,"depth":40,"text":673},"3. Scalability",{"id":368,"depth":40,"text":675},"4. Data Flow",{"id":419,"depth":40,"text":677},"5. Database Design",{"id":443,"depth":40,"text":679},"6. Reliability",{"id":461,"depth":31,"text":464},{"id":594,"depth":31,"text":597},{"id":643,"depth":31,"text":646},"markdown","content:courses:02-frontend-system-design.md","content","courses/02-frontend-system-design.md","courses/02-frontend-system-design","md",{"loc":4},1758003355768]